Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:23,930 --> 00:00:31,230
<i>[December 1988]
[Seoul, Dobong-gu, Ssangmundong]</i>

3
00:01:20,930 --> 00:01:21,930
Oh!

4
00:01:22,730 --> 00:01:24,330
Mr. Choi!

5
00:01:24,330 --> 00:01:26,630
Where did you get such pretty gloves?

6
00:01:26,630 --> 00:01:29,330
Wow... did a lady friend
get them for you?

7
00:01:29,330 --> 00:01:32,430
I'm not crazy, right?
Those are actually pink, right?

8
00:01:32,430 --> 00:01:34,930
Where did you get those gloves?

9
00:01:34,930 --> 00:01:38,430
Taek gave them to me
as my birthday gift.

10
00:01:41,330 --> 00:01:44,030
Wow... our Taek is so cool.

11
00:01:44,030 --> 00:01:45,130
Wow!

12
00:01:45,130 --> 00:01:47,830
He bought his dad such pretty pink ones!

13
00:01:51,330 --> 00:01:52,630
<i>Here's the weather.</i>

14
00:01:52,630 --> 00:01:55,530
<i>A cold front is taking
over the entire country.</i>

15
00:01:55,530 --> 00:02:00,330
<i>The middle region of Korea will be
around negative ten degrees Celsius</i>

16
00:02:00,330 --> 00:02:04,830
<i>and in the Seoul region, it will go up to
about negative two degrees Celsius.</i>

17
00:02:28,330 --> 00:02:33,490
<i>[Episode 8: One Warm Remark]</i>

18
00:02:34,530 --> 00:02:37,030
Do you two think that I'm an idiot?

19
00:02:37,930 --> 00:02:39,230
No.

20
00:02:39,230 --> 00:02:41,030
This time, it's for real.

21
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:42,030
Hey.

22
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:43,630
Isn't it obvious?

23
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:46,030
He's totally crazy about you!

24
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:48,030
Of course he is.
Hey.

25
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:49,430
Why else would he come all the way

26
00:02:49,430 --> 00:02:51,630
to the McDonald's in Apgujung
from Ssangmundong?

27
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:53,730
He totally likes you!

28
00:02:56,130 --> 00:02:57,930
Congratulations, Duk Seon.

29
00:02:57,930 --> 00:03:00,030
You just got yourself
a boyfriend again.

30
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:01,130
Shut it!

31
00:03:01,130 --> 00:03:02,130
Pipe down, already.

32
00:03:02,130 --> 00:03:04,930
When I think about how humiliated
I was because of you two, I... geez!

33
00:03:07,130 --> 00:03:08,530
Hey.

34
00:03:08,530 --> 00:03:11,730
Also, what do you guys
even know about men anyway, huh?

35
00:03:14,930 --> 00:03:18,030
If you rush to conclusions
one more time, I'll end you!

36
00:03:18,030 --> 00:03:19,530
All right, already.

37
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:23,930
Hey, Joey Wang.

38
00:03:23,930 --> 00:03:25,330
Your hair color looks nice.

39
00:03:25,330 --> 00:03:26,530
What did you dye it with?

40
00:03:26,530 --> 00:03:27,730
Oh, this?

41
00:03:28,230 --> 00:03:30,030
Hydrogen peroxide.

42
00:03:30,030 --> 00:03:32,430
What?
You did that to your hair?

43
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:33,830
Just get it done at the salon!

44
00:03:33,830 --> 00:03:35,030
Hey.

45
00:03:35,030 --> 00:03:37,630
Why don't you stay out of this one,
Ms. Rich Girl?

46
00:03:37,630 --> 00:03:39,830
Us two, broke girls
are in the middle of talking.

47
00:03:39,830 --> 00:03:42,430
Wow, Sung Duk Seon!

48
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,930
You know the English word, "talking?"

49
00:03:43,930 --> 00:03:45,530
Are you kidding me?

50
00:03:45,530 --> 00:03:47,860
Should I dye my hair
during winter break, too?

51
00:03:47,860 --> 00:03:49,430
I have hydrogen peroxide at home.

52
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:51,230
Don't, don't.
Use something else.

53
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:53,530
My head hurts so much from the smell.

54
00:03:53,530 --> 00:03:55,230
Really?
What should I use, then?

55
00:03:55,230 --> 00:03:57,730
What else?

56
00:04:27,330 --> 00:04:29,030
Duk Seon.

57
00:04:29,030 --> 00:04:30,830
Where did you go this morning?

58
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:32,330
To meet the girls.

59
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:34,730
- What did you eat?
- Ddukbokki.

60
00:04:35,530 --> 00:04:37,630
Why?
Did something happen?

61
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:39,830
Never mind.

62
00:04:46,630 --> 00:04:48,630
What's with Mom?
Did something happen?

63
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:53,230
Apparently, 30,000 won
disappeared from her wallet.

64
00:04:54,030 --> 00:04:55,030
So?

65
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:56,630
It wasn't you?

66
00:05:00,330 --> 00:05:02,430
What does she take me for?

67
00:05:04,130 --> 00:05:07,330
Where's the hair dryer?

68
00:05:15,030 --> 00:05:17,430
Why are you digging through
someone else's wallet?

69
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:19,130
You call yourself
an older sister?

70
00:05:19,130 --> 00:05:20,930
How could you doubt
your younger sister?

71
00:05:21,130 --> 00:05:22,930
Here!
Happy?

72
00:05:22,930 --> 00:05:24,230
Huh?

73
00:05:24,930 --> 00:05:26,530
If it's not you, whatever.

74
00:05:32,430 --> 00:05:36,330
It wasn't me, Mom!
It really wasn't me!

75
00:05:36,330 --> 00:05:38,330
I didn't take it!

76
00:05:38,330 --> 00:05:40,930
I don't even know
where you keep your wallet!

77
00:05:40,930 --> 00:05:42,530
Why are you doubting me?

78
00:05:42,530 --> 00:05:46,530
I really didn't take it!
Really!

79
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:49,030
Okay, Duk Seon.
Okay.

80
00:05:49,030 --> 00:05:50,530
I'm sorry.

81
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:56,630
Want a sweet potato?

82
00:06:04,830 --> 00:06:06,930
Oh geez...

83
00:06:06,930 --> 00:06:08,230
Does it taste good?

84
00:06:08,730 --> 00:06:09,730
Yes.

85
00:06:10,330 --> 00:06:11,930
But Mom...

86
00:06:11,930 --> 00:06:13,130
Yes?

87
00:06:14,330 --> 00:06:16,230
It might be No Eul.

88
00:06:17,830 --> 00:06:20,230
He's the only one who
could have done it, right?

89
00:06:23,030 --> 00:06:25,300
Even if he did,
don't say anything to him.

90
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:28,330
He'll feel hurt by that
and go down a crooked path.

91
00:06:28,330 --> 00:06:33,330
He'll rebel because I suspected him.
Got it?

92
00:06:36,030 --> 00:06:37,030
Okay?

93
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,430
What about me, then?

94
00:06:40,630 --> 00:06:42,830
You're not worried about me
going down a crooked path?

95
00:06:46,030 --> 00:06:48,630
Bo Ra...
Have some sweet potatoes.

96
00:06:48,630 --> 00:06:49,730
What about me?

97
00:06:49,730 --> 00:06:53,930
I'm only a year older than him!
I feel hurt too, you know!

98
00:07:03,130 --> 00:07:04,930
Oh yeah.

99
00:07:04,930 --> 00:07:07,330
Isn't today the day that Jung Bong
gets the test results?

100
00:07:07,330 --> 00:07:08,530
Probably.

101
00:07:08,530 --> 00:07:10,130
I wonder how he did...

102
00:07:26,730 --> 00:07:30,130
We could have misheard.
I'll call them again.

103
00:07:30,130 --> 00:07:32,630
<i>I'm sorry.
You didn't pass.</i>

104
00:07:57,730 --> 00:07:59,230
I apologize.

105
00:08:00,430 --> 00:08:03,230
I have nothing to say.

106
00:08:03,730 --> 00:08:05,230
Geez.

107
00:08:05,230 --> 00:08:07,030
It's fine.

108
00:08:07,030 --> 00:08:09,330
You can just take it again. Right?

109
00:08:13,030 --> 00:08:16,030
Geez, you're going to cause an earthquake
with your tremendous sighs!

110
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:19,340
What's on your head? Is it Sports Day?
Are you cheering for the white team?

111
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:22,130
Jung Bong.
Go to your room and rest.

112
00:08:22,130 --> 00:08:24,330
You're being hospitalized tomorrow.
It's no good for you to be stressed.

113
00:08:24,330 --> 00:08:26,230
Hurry!
Go to your room!

114
00:08:35,630 --> 00:08:39,030
It's fine!
Chin up, okay?

115
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:41,500
Kim Jung Bong!
These things happen!

116
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:43,500
They call it an exam
because you might fail!

117
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:47,130
It wouldn't be an exam if everyone
passed every time! It's okay! Okay?

118
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:53,130
If only he wasn't getting surgery...

119
00:08:54,330 --> 00:08:57,030
Even so, he grew up so well.

120
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:59,130
I'm thankful, even just for that.

121
00:09:00,730 --> 00:09:04,430
You sure are hard to please.

122
00:09:04,430 --> 00:09:06,530
Did you forget everything already?

123
00:09:06,530 --> 00:09:07,930
No...

124
00:09:11,330 --> 00:09:14,030
Honey, leave the house
for about two hours.

125
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,930
Go to Mr. Choi's
jewelry shop or something.

126
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,030
And what will you be doing?

127
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,630
The lady from Amore is coming.

128
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:20,330
Just go play outside for two hours.

129
00:09:20,330 --> 00:09:21,730
Are you going to buy makeup again?

130
00:09:21,730 --> 00:09:24,730
Just leave!

131
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:25,830
Okay, okay.
I'm going.

132
00:09:25,830 --> 00:09:28,530
But why two hours?
Doesn't it usually only last an hour?

133
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:31,630
The woman from Jutanhak is coming too.

134
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:33,820
Oh.

135
00:09:37,330 --> 00:09:38,330
Oh.

136
00:09:39,930 --> 00:09:41,530
Oh, really?

137
00:09:43,530 --> 00:09:45,330
Yeah, I ate.

138
00:09:46,830 --> 00:09:48,630
Where would I go, on a weekend?

139
00:09:49,330 --> 00:09:51,330
No. I told you,
I'm not going.

140
00:09:52,730 --> 00:09:54,430
You're going?

141
00:09:55,130 --> 00:09:56,730
It can't be helped then.

142
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:01,130
We can just meet up next week.

143
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:02,930
Don't be disappointed that
I'm not asking you not to go.

144
00:10:02,930 --> 00:10:05,530
I thought you were going because
you had something to take care of.

145
00:10:05,530 --> 00:10:07,130
I told you, go ahead.

146
00:10:07,630 --> 00:10:09,030
I'll be fine.

147
00:10:09,030 --> 00:10:10,630
<i>What?</i>

148
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:13,230
Hurry it up.
I'm expecting a call.

149
00:10:14,330 --> 00:10:15,430
Yeah.

150
00:10:15,430 --> 00:10:18,230
Okay.
See you next week.

151
00:10:18,230 --> 00:10:19,230
Okay.

152
00:10:21,130 --> 00:10:23,130
Who would you be expecting a call from?

153
00:10:23,130 --> 00:10:26,130
Dong Ryong! We're going to watch
the Pop Top Ten together today.

154
00:10:26,130 --> 00:10:29,030
When did you guys ever
call before meeting up?

155
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:34,311
Hello?

156
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:38,480
Hello?

157
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:41,680
Oh, Hwang Hee Soo?
What's up?

158
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:43,780
Right now?

159
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,680
Hi, Bo Ra.

160
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:51,280
That's "hello" to you, punk.

161
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,380
Hello.

162
00:10:56,580 --> 00:10:58,180
Are you going somewhere?

163
00:10:58,980 --> 00:11:00,680
I'm going to see my boyfriend.

164
00:11:06,380 --> 00:11:09,700
Oh, top-of-the-morning to you!

165
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:11,580
Greet me properly, damn it!

166
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:13,480
Yes, ma'am.
Sorry, ma'am.

167
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,680
Watch yourself, kid.

168
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:16,280
I will indeed watch myself, ma'am!

169
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,680
You like her, even when she's like that?

170
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,200
Not that attitude in particular.

171
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:24,580
Right?

172
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:26,380
You're human after all, too, huh?

173
00:11:26,380 --> 00:11:29,180
What are you going to do? She says
she's going to see her boyfriend.

174
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:31,650
No, she isn't.

175
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:34,080
When she goes to meet her boyfriend,
she always wears a skirt.

176
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,380
But look.
She wore pants.

177
00:11:35,380 --> 00:11:37,180
She just lied on purpose,
for me to hear.

178
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:42,400
Geez... that freak.

179
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:44,280
He freaks me out.

180
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:03,780
She's not human.

181
00:12:03,780 --> 00:12:05,080
What is she then?

182
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,980
A daffodil...

183
00:12:06,980 --> 00:12:08,680
Crazy bastard.

184
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:10,380
You've moved on
from Joey Wang, then?

185
00:12:10,380 --> 00:12:12,260
Yeah.
Ji Yeon's the best.

186
00:12:12,260 --> 00:12:14,480
She's not really my type.

187
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:17,280
Yeah, of course not.

188
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:19,980
What?

189
00:12:20,780 --> 00:12:22,680
This bastard is into aggressive girls.

190
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:26,380
You know, strong girls and such.

191
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:27,680
Yeah.

192
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:29,680
You know, someone like Bo Ra.

193
00:12:32,380 --> 00:12:33,380
What?

194
00:12:33,380 --> 00:12:35,880
Well, that's plausible.

195
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:39,180
But I'll bet that even she doesn't
act that way in front of her boyfriend.

196
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:41,980
What do you mean?

197
00:12:41,980 --> 00:12:44,680
Wow... you guys really
don't know anything.

198
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:46,980
All you know are formulas.
You know nothing about women.

199
00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:50,080
No matter how much girls fool around
and do the crab-leg dance at home

200
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:54,080
she'll be on her best behavior
in front of the guy she likes.

201
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:58,580
If a girl fools around or does
the crab-leg dance in front of you...

202
00:12:58,580 --> 00:13:01,180
that means that she doesn't
see you as a man.

203
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:03,580
If she did, she wouldn't be
act like that, no matter what.

204
00:13:03,580 --> 00:13:05,280
She'd be too embarrassed.

205
00:14:04,580 --> 00:14:05,780
<i>Who is it?</i>

206
00:14:05,780 --> 00:14:07,780
I'm the young lady from Amore!

207
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,580
Sun Young?

208
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:15,380
This feels so good...

209
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:21,480
- Wow... thanks to you...
- This is great...

210
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:22,980
She does it the best.

211
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:26,080
It feels so nice.

212
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:28,380
Don't smile.
You'll get wrinkles.

213
00:14:29,580 --> 00:14:31,580
Your skin is so good!

214
00:14:31,580 --> 00:14:34,260
Maybe it's because you're
an affluent woman?

215
00:14:34,260 --> 00:14:35,980
She's always had great skin.

216
00:14:35,980 --> 00:14:38,080
Even so, she took such good care of it.

217
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:41,280
And it seems that
she never gets stressed out!

218
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:43,980
Well, figures, since
you live in such a big home.

219
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:46,080
What concerns could you possibly have?

220
00:14:47,380 --> 00:14:48,760
Does it really seem like that?

221
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:50,680
Of course!

222
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:55,480
You look like such an affluent woman
who's never suffered once in her life!

223
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:58,280
Wow... I'm so jealous!

224
00:14:58,280 --> 00:15:00,760
Does it really seem that way?

225
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:03,340
She really looks like someone
who's never suffered once in her life?

226
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:04,680
Yes!

227
00:15:05,580 --> 00:15:09,080
- Wow... you've succeeded!
- I'll say.

228
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:10,080
What do you mean?

229
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:13,080
Oh, nothing.

230
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,080
Oh yeah.

231
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:16,280
You're going to give us
a lot of samples today, right?

232
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:19,680
Of course! You bought all that makeup,
so of course I will!

233
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,910
Just give us 300 or so.

234
00:15:22,910 --> 00:15:25,080
Oh, my!

235
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:28,860
- Rock, papers, scissors, shoot!
- Rock, papers, scissors, shoot!

236
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:30,280
- All right!
- All right!

237
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:32,280
I'm not good at making ramen, though.

238
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:34,090
<i>[La Bamba]</i>

239
00:15:34,090 --> 00:15:37,340
Stop messing around. You make it every
day because of Jung Bong. Hurry up, go!

240
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:38,920
I'm hungry!
Hurry up!

241
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:40,580
Damn it...

242
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:43,580
Hey... it's been a while
since Taek's been home.

243
00:15:43,580 --> 00:15:46,300
Ramyun won't do. Let's just order in.
Okay? How about it?

244
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:48,780
- I want ramen.
- You little...

245
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:52,180
Don't turn it on until I get back,
all right? I haven't seen "La Bamba!"

246
00:15:52,180 --> 00:15:53,780
Hurry the hell up and go!

247
00:15:55,990 --> 00:16:08,010
<i>I've never been the same...
because I love my girl...</i>

248
00:16:09,180 --> 00:16:10,180
Oh yeah.

249
00:16:10,180 --> 00:16:12,130
You didn't forget about tomorrow...
right, Taek?

250
00:16:12,130 --> 00:16:15,270
Wow... look at you and
your selective memory.

251
00:16:15,270 --> 00:16:16,680
You forgot, didn't you?

252
00:16:17,980 --> 00:16:20,980
We're all going to see a movie
in Jongro tomorrow, remember?

253
00:16:22,210 --> 00:16:24,580
I bought the tickets
at the theater in Jongro.

254
00:16:24,580 --> 00:16:26,580
I stood in line for an hour!

255
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,580
I remember now.

256
00:16:28,580 --> 00:16:31,580
I have a competition tomorrow though,
and it'll be late when it's over.

257
00:16:31,580 --> 00:16:35,080
Hey, that's why we decided to see it
in the evening, in the first place!

258
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:36,280
Did you forget?

259
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:37,680
Oh yeah... you're right.

260
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:40,680
Yes, that's right, Master Choi Taek.
Do you even know where the theater is?

261
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:43,810
Yeah. I just have to go to Jongro.
The Dansungsa Theater... right?

262
00:16:43,810 --> 00:16:46,280
Yes, that's right...
but just wait for us at the club.

263
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:48,080
We'll come pick you up.

264
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:50,080
It's fine.
You think I can't even find a theater?

265
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:52,080
- Yep. You can't.
- Yep. You can't.

266
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:56,380
It's on the way to the theater anyway,
so we'll come get you.

267
00:16:56,380 --> 00:16:59,780
Don't take a taxi, get off somewhere
weird, and wander away again.

268
00:16:59,780 --> 00:17:00,980
Got it?

269
00:17:00,980 --> 00:17:04,180
Don't go wandering off,
and wait for me... okay, honey?

270
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:06,580
Hasn't it been forever
since you went to the movies?

271
00:17:06,580 --> 00:17:08,050
Not since we finished
graduated middle school, right?

272
00:17:08,050 --> 00:17:09,450
He went with me a while ago.

273
00:17:09,450 --> 00:17:12,080
Oh, really? Was it fun?
What did you watch?

274
00:17:12,080 --> 00:17:15,380
As if he'd know.
He slept through the whole thing.

275
00:17:15,380 --> 00:17:17,580
He'd stayed up two nights in a row
before he came.

276
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:55,480
<i>Who is it?</i>

277
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,780
I'm the lady from Jutanhak!

278
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:15,080
What the hell is this?

279
00:18:21,980 --> 00:18:24,280
I just tossed in
whatever was in the fridge.

280
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:26,280
That's how we make it at our place.

281
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:29,580
My older brother eats like this.

282
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,680
It tastes great!

283
00:18:33,180 --> 00:18:34,680
Thanks.

284
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,780
When is his surgery?

285
00:18:36,780 --> 00:18:39,580
This weekend.
He'll be hospitalized tomorrow.

286
00:18:39,580 --> 00:18:42,980
We all have to go visit him there.
Which hospital is it?

287
00:18:42,980 --> 00:18:45,280
No need for that... he's just
having a one-hour surgery.

288
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:46,280
You don't need to come.

289
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:49,080
One hour?
It only takes that long?

290
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:51,180
Didn't it take about ten hours last year?

291
00:18:51,180 --> 00:18:53,580
He had to get new valves that time.

292
00:18:53,580 --> 00:18:55,880
This time, they're just
changing the batteries in it.

293
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:59,380
What about his exam?
Did he get into college?

294
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:03,680
He failed.

295
00:19:04,980 --> 00:19:06,480
Your nose is bleeding.

296
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:10,980
I guess winter really has come.

297
00:19:14,080 --> 00:19:15,580
What if you're sick, too?

298
00:19:15,580 --> 00:19:16,980
What are you saying?

299
00:19:16,980 --> 00:19:19,180
He got a checkup,
but they said he's fine.

300
00:19:19,180 --> 00:19:22,180
They said it was his immune system.
He and his brother have weak bodies.

301
00:19:22,180 --> 00:19:24,680
Geez... I wonder how many perverted
things he saw for it to be this bad.

302
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,380
It's because of my immune system, okay?

303
00:19:26,380 --> 00:19:27,380
Good for you.

304
00:19:27,380 --> 00:19:29,680
You little...

305
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:32,180
Even so, I'll bet your mother
feels sad about it.

306
00:19:32,180 --> 00:19:34,480
Even if it's a simple surgery.

307
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:37,580
Who?
My mom?

308
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:39,880
We're talking about Ms. Ra here.

309
00:19:42,190 --> 00:19:44,080
- Wow, feels great!
- My face feels so soft.

310
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:45,980
Sun Young, look at my face!
How does it look?

311
00:19:45,980 --> 00:19:48,580
You look beautiful!

312
00:19:48,580 --> 00:19:53,080
Thanks!
You look pretty, too!

313
00:19:53,580 --> 00:19:55,980
I feel like an affluent woman!

314
00:19:55,980 --> 00:19:58,480
Wow... look at your hands!

315
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:00,980
Wow... they're so soft!

316
00:20:00,980 --> 00:20:04,180
I'll bet this lady lives like a queen!

317
00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:06,600
Why do you say that?

318
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:10,760
Your hands are so soft. It looks
like they've never touched cold water.

319
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:12,480
Isn't that right?

320
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:15,690
And you have no worry lines
on your face either!

321
00:20:15,690 --> 00:20:18,380
I'm so jealous!

322
00:20:18,380 --> 00:20:21,180
Oh my... even it's just flattery,
it's nice to hear.

323
00:20:21,180 --> 00:20:23,680
What do you mean?
It's as clear as day, here!

324
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:27,280
But... you're going to give us
a lot of samples, right?

325
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:29,680
The young lady from Amore left us a ton!

326
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:32,280
Oh, of course!
I'll leave you a ton!

327
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:34,480
You bought so much at once, after all!

328
00:20:35,180 --> 00:20:37,280
Just leave us 300 or so.

329
00:20:45,380 --> 00:20:47,580
Let me see your face.

330
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:51,180
Wow, you're glowing!

331
00:20:51,180 --> 00:20:52,580
No matter how I look at you

332
00:20:52,580 --> 00:20:55,280
you're not the same person
you were three years ago.

333
00:20:56,280 --> 00:20:59,180
Is there anyone who has
suffered as much as you?

334
00:20:59,180 --> 00:21:03,080
Just ask anyone who has suffered
more than you to step forward!

335
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:05,880
Words can't express
just how much you've suffered.

336
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:08,680
Geez... yeah.
Strange things happen in life, huh?

337
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:12,780
I can't believe they'd say such things.

338
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:17,380
You suffered so much
when Jung Bong got sick.

339
00:21:18,180 --> 00:21:21,180
Wow.
You're really a fighter.

340
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:24,580
You'd leave Jung Bong at home to go work.

341
00:21:24,580 --> 00:21:26,380
You used to wallpaper
people's walls, right?

342
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:29,580
Well... yeah, I'd do that,
and I would deliver newspapers.

343
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:31,580
And I worked at a restaurant.

344
00:21:31,580 --> 00:21:33,580
You're really incredible.

345
00:21:33,580 --> 00:21:37,480
If someone told me my child had
heart disease, I'd pass out right there.

346
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:39,980
What else was I supposed to do?

347
00:21:39,980 --> 00:21:42,580
He had to get surgery,
but I had no money.

348
00:21:42,580 --> 00:21:44,580
I had to earn money any way I could.

349
00:21:44,580 --> 00:21:48,180
There were times that my husband and I
starved for a day or two, too.

350
00:21:48,180 --> 00:21:50,780
Wow... and you didn't even tell me!

351
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:52,090
You're really something!

352
00:21:52,090 --> 00:21:54,680
It's not like I was the only poor one.
You two had it worse.

353
00:21:57,280 --> 00:21:58,280
Well, yes.

354
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:01,080
Oh, yeah. What kind of surgery
is he getting this time?

355
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:04,980
Didn't he get a new valve
or something last time?

356
00:22:04,980 --> 00:22:08,580
Yeah. He got that surgery last year.

357
00:22:08,580 --> 00:22:10,680
Why does he need surgery again?

358
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:12,580
Oh, it's a simple one this time around.

359
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:15,180
There's a battery-like thing inside,
and they need to swap it.

360
00:22:15,180 --> 00:22:17,780
It'll be about... an hour?
Two, if it takes a long time.

361
00:22:17,780 --> 00:22:19,050
It'll be over quickly, then.

362
00:22:19,050 --> 00:22:20,680
Yeah.

363
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:25,180
Wow... even so, if my child were
getting surgery, simple as it may be...

364
00:22:25,180 --> 00:22:29,290
I'd be so nervous,
I wouldn't able to eat anything!

365
00:22:29,290 --> 00:22:31,280
Why worry?

366
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:34,880
We have money now, so the best doctor
in Korea is operating on him.

367
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:36,480
There's nothing to worry about.

368
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:40,680
Wow... you're such a tough one!

369
00:22:40,680 --> 00:22:43,180
That's how she managed to endure
during those hard times!

370
00:22:43,180 --> 00:22:45,580
Otherwise, you would've
gone mad already, right?

371
00:22:45,580 --> 00:22:46,580
Exactly.

372
00:22:47,280 --> 00:22:49,480
But where's Jung Bong?
Where did he go?

373
00:24:13,180 --> 00:24:16,380
Hey. We've heard all the songs
on the LP already.

374
00:24:16,380 --> 00:24:17,880
Hurry up and spill it.

375
00:24:23,380 --> 00:24:25,080
What is it?

376
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:27,180
What's so bad that
you can't tell a friend?

377
00:24:29,380 --> 00:24:30,880
Bo Ra.

378
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:31,880
Yeah?

379
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:33,980
Um... about Jong Hoon...

380
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:36,780
Jong Hoon?

381
00:24:37,380 --> 00:24:39,180
Um, no...
I mean, upperclassman Jong Hoon.

382
00:24:41,180 --> 00:24:42,280
What is this?

383
00:24:42,780 --> 00:24:45,380
Why are you referring to
my boyfriend so casually?

384
00:24:45,380 --> 00:24:47,380
There's really nothing between us.

385
00:24:47,380 --> 00:24:48,580
What do you mean?

386
00:24:48,580 --> 00:24:50,780
Did something happen
between you two?

387
00:24:54,780 --> 00:24:58,980
I felt that you should know,
no matter what.

388
00:24:58,980 --> 00:25:03,280
On the day you couldn't go on the
retreat because of family issues...

389
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:07,380
I had a lot to drink that day.

390
00:25:07,380 --> 00:25:12,280
I drank a lot, and upperclassman
Jong Hoon was really drunk too.

391
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:13,480
And so?

392
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:19,080
I went out for a bit
to get some fresh air...

393
00:25:20,080 --> 00:25:24,380
and upperclassman Jong Hoon followed
me out, saying his head hurt too.

394
00:25:24,380 --> 00:25:25,880
Did you two kiss?

395
00:25:35,880 --> 00:25:37,580
I'm sorry, Bo Ra.

396
00:25:38,380 --> 00:25:40,180
It was honestly a mistake!

397
00:25:40,180 --> 00:25:43,080
The two of us were way too drunk.
We weren't in our right minds.

398
00:25:44,780 --> 00:25:46,780
I'm really sorry.

399
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:56,180
I felt so bad, I couldn't even
look you in the eyes properly.

400
00:25:58,980 --> 00:26:01,680
Even so, you're my friend, so...

401
00:26:02,380 --> 00:26:04,480
you're my best friend, so...

402
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:06,880
I couldn't just keep quiet
and let it slide.

403
00:26:08,180 --> 00:26:09,280
Bo Ra!

404
00:26:10,380 --> 00:26:11,880
I'm sorry.
Really.

405
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:12,880
It's fine.

406
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,780
I'm not going to associate
myself with him anymore.

407
00:26:15,780 --> 00:26:17,680
So don't cry.

408
00:26:23,410 --> 00:26:25,780
And I'm not associating myself
with you anymore, either.

409
00:26:25,780 --> 00:26:27,380
Friend?

410
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:29,380
As if.

411
00:26:38,070 --> 00:26:45,980
<i>Buckwheat jelly for sale!</i>

412
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:50,280
<i>Buckwheat jelly for sale!</i>

413
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,580
No Eul, what time is it now?

414
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:59,480
I bet your dad is having
a drink somewhere again.

415
00:27:00,580 --> 00:27:03,480
Geez... what a wretched fate...

416
00:27:05,780 --> 00:27:07,280
My Il Hwa!

417
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:09,180
I'm home!

418
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:13,080
Hey. Your hubby is here!

419
00:27:13,080 --> 00:27:15,980
You're at it again! You drank up a storm,
didn't you?

420
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:21,780
Geez... is that any way
to talk to your husband?

421
00:27:22,580 --> 00:27:25,180
I really tried to come home early today

422
00:27:25,180 --> 00:27:28,380
but there was something really important
to be done at the bank, so...

423
00:27:28,380 --> 00:27:32,580
it couldn't be helped,
and I just had one drink.

424
00:27:32,580 --> 00:27:36,580
Work, my ass! How is it that you have to
work overtime every single day?

425
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:40,380
And just what is that, now?

426
00:27:40,380 --> 00:27:44,880
This is a liquid that erases ink!

427
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:47,980
It's the first time you've seen
such a thing, right?

428
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:51,240
So, uh...

429
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:54,490
I was taking the subway
on my way home

430
00:27:54,580 --> 00:27:59,680
and I saw a kid,
about No Eul's age, selling these!

431
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,380
Oh my, oh my...

432
00:28:01,380 --> 00:28:06,880
You know as well as I do that
I usually don't buy this kind of stuff!

433
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:11,280
But they said that this
really erases ink!

434
00:28:11,280 --> 00:28:15,380
I would've regretted it if I didn't
buy it, so I bought just one.

435
00:28:15,380 --> 00:28:18,580
And then... I bought just one more!

436
00:28:18,580 --> 00:28:23,580
And then, just... three!

437
00:28:28,780 --> 00:28:30,580
Wait a minute.
Where's the ink?

438
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:34,080
Let's just see.

439
00:28:47,580 --> 00:28:50,180
It's okay!

440
00:28:50,180 --> 00:28:54,380
I can just get it out
with this stuff!

441
00:28:54,380 --> 00:28:57,380
Just watch! Just watch.

442
00:28:57,380 --> 00:29:01,080
You take this here, and
do this, and then... this.

443
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:04,380
You just sprinkle it on here,
like so. Rub, rub, rub, rub!

444
00:29:04,380 --> 00:29:10,080
And then, you just rub it in!
Like this! Rub, rub, rub, rub.

445
00:29:10,080 --> 00:29:12,310
Rub, rub, rub, rub!

446
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:22,930
This is weird... it worked so well
during the demo on the subway.

447
00:29:22,930 --> 00:29:26,380
Geez... you half-wit! Half-wit!

448
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:30,880
How can you call your husband that?
A half-wit? A half-wit?

449
00:29:30,880 --> 00:29:34,000
What else would you be then?
You idiot!

450
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:36,200
Huh?
What does that mean?

451
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:38,280
I'm calling you an idiot, stupid!

452
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:44,010
How dare you call your husband an idiot?
Why I ought to--

453
00:29:44,010 --> 00:29:46,760
Wow, what a saint we have here!

454
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:48,660
How many years ago
was your last promotion?

455
00:29:48,660 --> 00:29:50,360
Why the hell are you
bringing that up now?

456
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:54,960
What does that have
to do with this liquid?

457
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:58,060
If you had performed
your wifely duties better

458
00:29:58,060 --> 00:29:59,960
I would have kept on
being promoted by now--

459
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:02,860
Promoted, my ass!

460
00:30:02,860 --> 00:30:07,810
My ass? My ass?
How dare you talk to me that way?

461
00:30:07,810 --> 00:30:09,180
Yeah, you heard me!

462
00:30:09,180 --> 00:30:10,760
If only... imagine you didn't
rack up all that debt?

463
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:13,260
Would we still be living like this,
in a half-basement? Huh?

464
00:30:13,260 --> 00:30:17,460
Why are you bringing up
irrelevant things again?

465
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:20,660
I dare you to say that again!
I'll kill you!

466
00:30:20,660 --> 00:30:21,760
What did you say?

467
00:30:21,760 --> 00:30:24,360
What did you say you'd do to me?

468
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:27,060
Go ahead and try to kill me, then!
Go ahead!

469
00:30:27,060 --> 00:30:28,860
- What are you doing?
- Go ahead!

470
00:30:28,860 --> 00:30:29,860
You must be out of your mind!

471
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:31,460
Just try and kill me!

472
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:46,460
Are you... okay?

473
00:30:46,460 --> 00:30:48,460
What do we do?

474
00:30:48,460 --> 00:30:50,560
Can you see with that eye?

475
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:51,960
How many fingers am I holding up?

476
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:53,560
Try and count them.

477
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:54,960
I'll kill you...

478
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:09,960
What's all this, Big Bro?

479
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:12,660
This is my other half.

480
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:23,760
These are my Rubik's cubes...

481
00:31:24,660 --> 00:31:28,460
And this is my stamp collection.

482
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:36,460
And these are my
Campus Music Festival LPs.

483
00:31:37,060 --> 00:31:42,760
And these are all the
movie posters I've collected.

484
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:51,960
And this is... my journal.

485
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:55,760
I'll give you all of this.

486
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:57,460
I don't need any of this anymore.

487
00:31:59,460 --> 00:32:02,060
Geez... quit overreacting!

488
00:32:02,060 --> 00:32:05,160
Why are you making such a big deal
over an hour-long surgery?

489
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:09,760
Even so, surgery is surgery.

490
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:11,560
Big Bro.

491
00:32:11,560 --> 00:32:14,460
They say that the chances of the surgery
failing are less than three percent.

492
00:32:14,460 --> 00:32:15,960
I looked into it already.

493
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:25,360
The chance of getting heart disease when
you're young is less than two percent.

494
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:31,660
That's why... I'm so scared of
that three percent chance.

495
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:50,160
Geez...

496
00:32:50,660 --> 00:32:53,560
Stop overreacting!

497
00:32:54,460 --> 00:32:57,660
Big Bro! They say that it's a surgery
that doctors can do with their eyes shut.

498
00:32:57,660 --> 00:32:59,960
Stop saying silly things
and go to sleep already.

499
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:03,960
Want to sleep with me tonight,
Little Bro?

500
00:33:06,460 --> 00:33:08,260
That's a little...

501
00:33:08,260 --> 00:33:11,160
Yeah.
I'm not too keen on it, either.

502
00:33:42,460 --> 00:33:43,760
I'm home.

503
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:45,560
Oh, you're home?
Hurry and wash up.

504
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:46,660
Are you hungry?

505
00:33:46,660 --> 00:33:47,860
I'm fine.

506
00:33:49,140 --> 00:33:53,760
Oh my God, oh my God.
I'm totally hungry!

507
00:33:53,760 --> 00:33:55,060
Want to eat red bean porridge?

508
00:33:55,060 --> 00:33:56,060
Yeah.

509
00:33:56,560 --> 00:33:58,460
Honey.

